# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics in the YojaK-Frontend React + Vite project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/analytics` package (version ^1.6.1) to the project dependencies

### 2. Modified Files

#### `src/App.jsx`
- **Import Added**: Imported the `Analytics` component from `@vercel/analytics/react`
- **Component Added**: Added `<Analytics />` component at the root level of the App component, just after the `<ClerkLoaded>` wrapper
- This ensures analytics tracking is active across all routes and pages in the application

#### `package.json`
- Added `@vercel/analytics` to the dependencies list

#### `package-lock.json`
- Updated with the new dependency tree for @vercel/analytics and its 218 sub-dependencies

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel Web Analytics guide for React applications:
- Used the `@vercel/analytics/react` package variant which is appropriate for React + Vite projects
- Placed the Analytics component at the root level to ensure it tracks all page views and routes
- The component is positioned after `ClerkLoaded` to ensure authentication state is loaded before analytics tracking begins

## Testing & Verification

1. ✅ **Build Test**: Successfully ran `npm run build` - build completed without errors
2. ✅ **Linter Check**: Ran `npm run lint` - no new linting errors introduced (pre-existing errors in other files remain unchanged)
3. ✅ **Package Installation**: All 218 packages installed successfully with no vulnerabilities

## How It Works

Once deployed to Vercel:
- The Analytics component will automatically track page views across all routes
- Data will be visible in the Vercel Dashboard under the Analytics tab
- A Fetch/XHR request to `/_vercel/insights/view` will be visible in the browser's Network tab when visiting any page

## Next Steps for the User

After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel Dashboard (Project → Analytics tab → Enable)
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. View analytics data in the Vercel Dashboard

## Files Modified
- `src/App.jsx` - Added Analytics component import and usage
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency tree
